Frequently Asked Questions

What is your typical project timeline?

Project timelines vary based on scope and complexity. Small projects typically take 2-4 weeks, while larger applications may take 2-3 months. I provide detailed timelines during the discovery phase.

Do you offer retainer or ongoing support?

Yes, I offer flexible retainer packages for ongoing maintenance, improvements, and support. This is perfect for long-term partnerships.

What is your process for working with clients?

I follow a structured process: Discovery → Planning → Development → Launch & Support. I maintain regular communication and provide updates throughout.

Can you work with existing codebases?

Absolutely. I can audit existing projects, provide improvements, add new features, or refactor for better performance and maintainability.

Do you provide training and documentation?

Yes, I provide comprehensive documentation and can offer training sessions to help your team understand and maintain the project.

How do you handle project changes and revisions?

I build flexibility into project planning. Minor changes are included in the scope. Significant changes are scoped separately with updated timelines and pricing.
